Class ResourceIdentifier

java.lang.Object
com.tectonica.jonix.onix3.ResourceIdentifier
All Implemented Interfaces:
OnixComposite, OnixComposite.OnixDataComposite<JonixResourceIdentifier>, OnixComposite.OnixDataCompositeWithKey<JonixResourceIdentifier,ResourceIdentifierTypes>, OnixTag, Serializable
public class ResourceIdentifier extends Object implements OnixComposite.OnixDataCompositeWithKey<JonixResourceIdentifier,ResourceIdentifierTypes>, Serializable

Resource identifier composite

A group of data elements which together specify an identifier of the resource, in accordance with the specified scheme. The composite is optional, and repeatable to specify multiple identifiers for the resource, but may only be used when <ResourceFileLink> is present.

Reference name <ResourceIdentifier>
Short tag <resourceidentifier>
Cardinality 0…n

Technical notes about <ResourceIdentifier> from the schema author: Unique identifier for a resource required for manufacturing or packaging of the product. Note this is likely to be a proprietary identifer used for disambiguation by the resource creator ● Added at revision 3.0.8 This tag may be included in the following composites:

  • <CoverResource>
  • <BodyResource>
  • <InsertResource>
Possible placements within ONIX message:
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ SupplementManifest ⯈ CoverManifest ⯈ CoverResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ CoverManifest ⯈ CoverResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ SupplementManifest ⯈ BodyManifest ⯈ BodyResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ BodyManifest ⯈ BodyResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ SupplementManifest ⯈ InsertManifest ⯈ InsertResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier
  • Product ⯈ ProductionDetail ⯈ ProductionManifest ⯈ InsertManifest ⯈ InsertResource ⯈ ResourceIdentifier

    • resourceIDType

      public ResourceIDType resourceIDType()

      An ONIX code identifying the scheme from which the identifier in <IDValue> is taken. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <ResourceIdentifier> composite, and non-repeating.

      JONIX adds: this field is required

    • idValue

      public IDValue idValue()

      An identifier of the type specified in the <ResourceIDType> element. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <ResourceIdentifier> composite, and non-repeating.

      JONIX adds: this field is required

    • idTypeName

      public IDTypeName idTypeName()

      A name which identifies a proprietary identifier scheme (ie a scheme which is not a standard and for which there is no individual ID type code). Must be included when, and only when, the code in <ResourceIDType> indicates a proprietary scheme, eg a publisher’s own identifier type. Optional and non-repeating.

      JONIX adds: this field is optional
